---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Affiliate Disclosure — AI Smart Tools"
  description="Our FTC-compliant affiliate disclosure. How we make money, and how we keep editorial independence."
>
  <article class="container-prose py-12 md:py-16 prose-custom">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Affiliate Disclosure</h1>
    
    <p class="lead">
      In accordance with the Federal Trade Commission's 16 CFR Part 255, this page discloses the affiliate relationships that fund AI Smart Tools.
    </p>
    
    <h2>What is an affiliate link?</h2>
    <p>
      Some links on AI Smart Tools are "affiliate links." This means if you click one and sign up for the product, we may receive a commission from the vendor. You pay nothing extra.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Which links are affiliate links?</h2>
    <p>
      Affiliate links are tagged with <code>rel="sponsored"</code> in the HTML so browsers can identify them. They appear on:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Product reviews (e.g. "Otter.ai Review")</li>
      <li>Comparison pages (e.g. "Notion vs Obsidian")</li>
      <li>Best-of lists (e.g. "Best AI Meeting Notes Tools")</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>How does this affect editorial?</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>It doesn't.</strong> Our editorial scores are independent of whether a product has an affiliate program.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Tools with no affiliate program still get reviewed.</li>
      <li>Tools with low commission rates still get reviewed.</li>
      <li>We do not inflate ratings to earn more commission.</li>
      <li>If a tool is bad, we say so. If a tool is good, we say that too.</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Disclosure of conflict of interest</h2>
    <p>
      AI Smart Tools team members may use the products we review. We disclose these in the relevant review article.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Questions?</h2>
    <p>
      Email <a href="mailto:disclosure@aismarttools.com">disclosure@aismarttools.com</a>.
    </p>
    
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-8">Last updated: July 19, 2026.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
